May Contain Sesame. Non-GMO! You are about to experience something simple made extraordinary. This Baguette is made from a palette of five simple ingredients: flour, water, salt, yeast, and malted barley flour. Then it is baked in a stone-deck oven (notice the floured bottom), leaving us with a golden, crisp crust and soft, flavourful interior.

We are also proud to share that while we have always been committed to uncompromised artisan baking, we have the Non-GMO project Verified™ seal to prove it.
Suggested Use/Directions:
One-Day Freshness?
You will notice this bread stays fresh for one day. That's because there are no preservatives or dough conditioners in any of our products. Here are some tips to maximize you ACE Bakery® Baguette experience.

Today:
Eat as much as you can for the rest of the day.
Tip: Tear a little off the top while shopping!

Tomorrow:
A little stale Run it under cold water for 5 seconds, and place in a 350°F oven for 5 minutes, or until crisp. Or cube, drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with salt, pepper, minced garlic, and Parmesan.
Toast in a 350°F oven for 3-5 minutes. Serve as croutons.

Day After Tomorrow:
Smash into bread crumbs and add seasonings of your choice.

This Bread Freezes Really Well
Wrap and seal tightly in a good quality freezer bag.
To reheat, remove the bread from the bag and, while still frozen, place in a 400°F oven for 6-8 minutes, or until heated throughout
